Directory that contains *.def files for 3D simulations.

run.def		: main default files for LMDZ driver
LX.def		: vertical grid where X is the number of levels
gcm*def		: parameters for the 3D dynamical core
orchidee.def	: for continental surfaces
config.def	: configuration setup (model, forcing, outputs ...)
traceur.def	: control of advected trace species
guide.def	: control of nudging
physiq.def	: corresponds to PHYS/physiq.def_NPv6.0.12split

PHYS directory
--------------
The "PHYS" directory contains various default files for various configurations
of the physical package :
AR4			: 2005-2013 - used for CMIP3 (IPSL-CM4 [1]) and CMIP5 (IPSL-CM5A, [2])
NPv0.0			: first "new physics" version ~ 2005
NPv1.0
NPv2.0
NPv3.0
NPv3.1			: 2012 - "new physics" used for CMIP5 (IPSL-CM5B, [3])
NPv3.2			: 2014 - more stable numerical schemes in the boundary layer
NPv4.12			: 2014 - first version for CMIP6 = new physics + stoch. trig. + stratocu
NPv5.17h		: Jul 2015 - first long coupled simulations
NPv5.4			: Fev 2016 - new convective mixing (iflag_mix=1) -> ranifall variability
NPv5.5			: Apr 2016 - RRTM + Bergeron + increased turb. mix. length -> reduced call biases
NPv5.65			: Jun 2016 : (=6.0.4) tuning
NPv5.67			:            alternative tuning
NPv5.70			: Jul 2016 : (=6.0.5) vert. cloud PDF, tuning
NPv5.80b		:
NPv5.80bz0		:
NPv6.0.7		: Sep 2016
NPv6.0.8		:
NPv6.0.9		: Jan 2017 : tuning sub-grid orog. + physical timestep = 15 min (10 before)
NPv6.0.10		: Apr 2017 : convection conditioned by Ttop
NPv6.0.10fallv		: new boundary layer tuning (Vignon)
NPv6.0.12		: Jul 2017 tune of the final tuning for CMIP6
NPv6.0.12split		: Jul 2017 - IPSL-CM6 - thermals outside cold pools only (splitting)
NPv6.0.12ttop		: Jul 2017 - IPSL-CM6 - convection conditioned by ttop, close to NPv6.0.12
NPv6.0.11trigB		: Jul 2017 - alterantive tuning with different threshold on cumulus size for trig.


[1] F. Hourdin, I. Musat, S. Bony, P. Braconnot, F. Codron, J.-L. 
Dufresne, L. Fairhead, M.-A. Filiberti, P. Friedlingstein, J.-Y. 
Grandpeix, G. Krinner, P. LeVan, Z.-X. Li et F. Lott, 2006, The LMDZ4 
general circulatiuon model : climate performance and sensitivity to 
parametrized physics with emphasis on tropical convection,
Climate Dynamics, 27 : 787-813

[2] Hourdin, F., M.-A. Foujols, F. Codron, V. Guemas, J.-L. Dufresne, S. 
Bony, S. Denvil, L. Guez, F. Lott, J. Ghattas, P. Braconnot, O. Marti, Y. 
Meurdesoif, and L. Bopp, 2013a, Impact of the LMDZ atmospheric grid 
configuration on the climate and sensitivity of the IPSL-CM5A coupled 
model, Clim. Dyn., 40, 2167–2192, 2013a.

[3] Hourdin, F., J.-Y. Grandpeix, C. Rio, S. Bony, A. Jam, F. Cheruy, N. 
Rochetin, L. Fairhead, A. Idelkadi, I. Musat, J.-L. Dufresne, A. Lahellec, 
M.-P. Lefebvre, and R. Roehrig, 2013b, LMDZ5B: the atmospheric component 
of the IPSL climate model with revisited parameterizations for clouds and 
convection, Clim. Dyn., 40, 2193–2222, 2013b.
